  stimulus_text = 'The first time humans landed on the moon was a momentous occasion.  However, the journey, beginning in 1961, was a long and arduous one. Many people worked tirelessly for years to get humans to the moon. And the success of the Apollo 11 mission is a credit to the many individuals whose work made it possible. Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
